parameters:
May 18, 1976: From tomorrow, I will undertake the austere
practices of Shugendo. It's a grueling ten-day training, but
it's an important act to cultivate spiritual power to calm
the spirits that torment the living.
I must continue to work hard and catch up to my master.

June 2, 1976: I feel a slight increase in my spiritual
power. The daily purification and meditation seem to be
effective. Tomorrow, I will face my first exorcism. I want
to prove that I can save people.

February 3, 1979: The master has disappeared. He went out to
exorcise a significant curse he had planned to confront for
some time and hasn't returned for two months.

Could it be that the master was defeated? And I have yet to
repay him for saving me.

August 7, 1981: Today is an extremely hot day. I managed to
find an elderly psychic who knows clues about the master,
but I was told I'm not strong enough to challenge the
mansion.

Even his disciple, who was called a genius, never returned
after challenging the mansion. It's known as the "Cursed
Moon Mansion" in those circles, and even mentioning its name
is avoided.

September 20, 1983: I found a shrine in the mountains. The
decayed shrine is filled with a horrific curse. Perhaps its
deity was also consumed by the "Cursed Moon Mansion."
Can I overcome a curse that even gods have succumbed to?

January 9, 1987: At last, I will challenge the mansion. I
found a path that leads to it from within the city. Now that
I have surpassed my master's power and become a psychic
known to all in the area, I have honed my spiritual power.

The time has come for me to avenge my master and lift the
longstanding curse.

Nothing is written beyond this point.
